data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0ad8afe36ac08139006998cebfcc188194ab67e3fb5916b34c","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":158,"text":"**Foundry Agent Service** is Microsoft’s managed runtime in **Microsoft Foundry (Azure AI Foundry)** for building and running **production-ready AI agents**—not just chatbots, but agents that can **decide**, **use tools**, and **execute workflow steps** reliably in real applications. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic))\n\n### What it does (in practical terms)\n- **Runs the agent** end-to-end: manages *conversations/threads*, *runs*, and *tool invocations* so you don’t have to glue all the infrastructure together yourself. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n- **Orchestrates tool use**: the model can choose from configured tools (knowledge + actions) to fetch grounded context or perform tasks. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n- **Adds “production” capabilities**: integrates with enterprise concerns like **identity, networking, observability**, and **content safety/policy enforcement**, to help move beyond demos. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n\n### Tools you can plug into agents\nFoundry Agent Service supports a catalog of built-in and bring-your-own tools, commonly grouped as: ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n- **Knowledge tools** (to ground responses in data): e.g., Azure AI Search / File Search / Fabric, and public web grounding options. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n- **Action tools** (to do things): e.g., Azure Logic Apps, OpenAPI spec tool, MCP endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, “Deep Research”, and browser automation. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n\n### Web grounding (real-time info) options\nIf you need your agent to reference current public web information, Foundry includes Bing-based grounding tools:\n- **Grounding with Bing Search**: agent can decide to call Bing, get relevant “chunks,” and return an answer **with citations** and a reference to the Bing query; Microsoft has specific “use and display requirements.” ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/bing-grounding?view=foundry-classic))  \n- **Grounding with Bing Custom Search (preview)**: restrict web grounding to a **configured allowlist of domains**; note this can transfer customer data outside the Azure compliance boundary and may have separate terms/costs. ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/bing-custom-search?view=foundry-classic))  \n\n### “Classic” vs “new” experience\nMicrosoft’s docs note there are **classic** and **new** portal/API experiences, and some pages are explicitly labeled as “classic,” with newer equivalents (for example, a newer “Web Search tool (preview)” is recommended in some contexts). ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic))  \n\nIf you tell me whether you’re using **the new Foundry portal/API or the classic one**, and what you’re trying to build (support agent, RAG over internal docs, workflow automation, etc.), I can point you to the right setup path and the best tool choices."}

